<task id="059" project="spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6">
  <metadata>
    <title>D-C-12 — Additive `context.*` PaneEventBus event types (ADR-015 binding: tool name + timestamp ONLY)</title>
    <status>completed</status>
    <estimated-effort>4 hours</estimated-effort>
    <phase>Phase C — Tri-directional Workspace (Pillar 6c)</phase>
    <wave>C-G2 (parallel after 6a)</wave>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <dependencies>053 (workspace state wired)</dependencies>
    <tags>frontend, typescript, ai-widgets, telemetry</tags>
    <rigor-level>FULL</rigor-level>
    <rigor-hint>FULL</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>ADR-015 binding event-shape definition; downstream telemetry emission (task 063) + widget render (task 061) BOTH depend on these types being correct.</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>C-G2</parallel-group>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Add the following additive event types on the existing `context` channel of
    PaneEventBus (per ADR-030 — 4 channels closed; additive types only; NO new channel):
    `context.tool_call_started`, `context.tool_call_completed`,
    `context.knowledge_retrieved`, `context.playbook_node_executing`,
    `context.playbook_node_completed`, `context.decision_made`.

    **ADR-015 BINDING (CRITICAL)**: trace events log tool name + decision + timestamp
    ONLY. NEVER user message text. Deterministic IDs (matterId, scopeId, playbookId,
    nodeId, toolName, knowledgeSourceId) acceptable. The event-type definitions
    themselves MUST type the payload such that user message content CANNOT be smuggled
    in — payload fields are explicit + enumerated. Each event payload includes
    `timestamp: string` (ISO-8601), `sessionId: string`, `correlationId?: string`. Knowledge
    retrievals include `knowledgeSourceId` + `relevanceScore` (numeric) but NOT the
    retrieved content body. Decisions include `decision: string` (short enum-like) +
    `decisionReason?: string` (machine summary, not user text).

    Define in `@spaarke/ai-widgets/src/events/PaneEventTypes.ts`. Discriminated union per
    event name. Type-check ensures consumers exhaustively handle each variant.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior TypeScript engineer with deep familiarity with PaneEventBus contract + ADR-030
    4-channel constraint + ADR-015 data-governance audit pattern.
  </role>

  <goal>
    Six new event types defined as discriminated union variants on the `context` channel.
    Types make user content leakage IMPOSSIBLE by construction. Type-check passes.
    Downstream tasks (061 widget + 063 telemetry emission) can import + use these types.
  </goal>

